    <h2 headingId="h.t2wd5494xnou">
      <t>Technical Approach</t>
    </h2>
    <p>
      <t>We will use a </t>
      <t>
        <b>diff-based reconciliation</b>
      </t>
      <t> strategy. This means comparing the </t>
      <t>
        <i>pristine state</i>
      </t>
      <t> against the </t>
      <t>
        <i>edited state</i>
      </t>
      <t> and computing minimal API requests.</t>
    </p>
    <p>
      <t>Key constraints:</t>
    </p>
    <li parent="kix.nw38s2ws4me4">
      <t>All index calculations must be precise</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.nw38s2ws4me4">
      <t>Bold and italic spans must not bleed across paragraph boundaries</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.nw38s2ws4me4">
      <t>Table cell edits are independent of body paragraph edits</t>
    </li>
    <h3 headingId="h.9mn671k3d8rc">
      <t>Implementation Notes</t>
    </h3>
    <p>
      <t>The reconciler processes elements in </t>
      <t>
        <b>document order</b>
      </t>
      <t>. Each paragraph is assigned an index based on its position in the linear content array.</t>
    </p>
    <table>
      <col class="tc2" />
      <col class="tc2" />
      <tr>
        <td>
          <p>
            <t>Operation</t>
          </p>
        </td>
        <td>
          <p>
            <t>Index Effect</t>
          </p>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <p>
            <t>insertText</t>
          </p>
        </td>
        <td>
          <p>
            <t>Shifts subsequent indices up</t>
          </p>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p>
      <t>Important: never mutate indices after they have been computed. Any insertion shifts subsequent indices.</t>
    </p>
    <h2 headingId="h.g9v68oco8iud">
      <t>Risks and Mitigations</t>
    </h2>
    <p>
      <t>The main risk is </t>
      <t>
        <b>index drift</b>
      </t>
      <t> — where the computed insertion point diverges from the actual document state after earlier insertions have been applied.</t>
    </p>
    <p>
      <t>We mitigate this by sorting all insertions in </t>
      <t>
        <i>reverse document order</i>
      </t>
      <t> so that later insertions do not affect earlier ones.</t>
    </p>
